translated: Häggberg, Axel Harald Waldemar, engineer, born on March 29, 1900 in Sanikt Lars, Östergötland, the first child of Axel H. and Augusta Johanson. Married in 1931 to Hervor Lundborig. He worked as a surveyor and master of shoring for the state railway construction from 1915-1925, roadmaster in Hanekind's road district from 1936-1936, head roadmaster in Valkebo road district from 1937-1943, chief engineer of road administration in Östergötland county from 1944-1946, and engineer in the road administration in Jönköping county since 1946. He was a member of Sweden's union of supervisors, Swedish motorist federation, Östergötland technical society, State railway construction comradeship association, and the image-making society of government employees. He was an Odd Fellow and served as chairman of Östergötland roadmaster association and reviewed the Swedish equivalent. He traveled to Denmark in 1931 and 1936, Norway in 1933, and Germany in 1936.
